channel.title: Anyone ever seen this?
channel.description:
I'm very confused here, I'm trying to compile a program, and finally got it compiled. I verify what type of file it is with file, but when I try to run it I get an odd message:
[code]$ file bin/gcc-4.4.3/debug/boost-source/link-static/runtime-link-static/threading-multi/client_test bin/gcc-4.4.3/debug/boost-source/link-static/runtime-link-static/threading-multi/client_test: ELF 32-bit LSB shared object, Intel 80386, version 1 (GNU/Linux), dynamically linked (uses shared libs), for GNU/Linux 2.6.15, not stripped $ ./bin/gcc-4.4.3/debug/boost-source/link-static/runtime-link-static/threading-multi/client_test -bash: ./bin/gcc-4.4.3/debug/boost-source/link-static/runtime-link-static/threading-multi/client_test: No such file or directory[/code]
Any ideas on why the file is obviously there, yet when I run it bash tells me it's not?

item.title: Anyone ever seen this?
item.dc:creator: @moparisthebest Moparisthebest
item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

SomethingToHide:

What happens if you backup a copy of it elsewhere, and then “touch client_test”, and then try it?

It’s not the name or the path, it’s the actual file, refer to the commands below.

Mopman:

what does ls -lq /the/directory/its/in show - are there any odd control chars in the file name?

No strange characters at all, it’s named client_test

$ ls client_test connection_tester dump_torrent enum_if fragmentation_test make_torrent simple_client src upnp_test.o client_test.o connection_tester.o dump_torrent.o enum_if.o fragmentation_test.o make_torrent.o simple_client.o upnp_test $ ./client_test -bash: ./client_test: No such file or directory $ ./simple_client -bash: ./simple_client: No such file or directory $ mv client_test client_test.bak $ ./client_test.bak -bash: ./client_test.bak: No such file or directory $ touch client_test $ ./client_test -bash: ./client_test: Permission denied $ chmod +x client_test $ ./client_test $ mv client_test.bak client_test $ ./client_test -bash: ./client_test: No such file or directory $ ls -lq total 256560 -rwxr-xr-x 1 mopar mopar 57718063 2010-12-26 11:49 client_test -rw-r--r-- 1 mopar mopar 1915580 2010-12-26 11:45 client_test.o -rwxr-xr-x 1 mopar mopar 9035112 2010-12-26 11:49 connection_tester -rw-r--r-- 1 mopar mopar 2227236 2010-12-26 11:49 connection_tester.o -rwxr-xr-x 1 mopar mopar 56836572 2010-12-26 11:49 dump_torrent -rw-r--r-- 1 mopar mopar 438676 2010-12-26 11:49 dump_torrent.o -rwxr-xr-x 1 mopar mopar 2408946 2010-12-26 11:49 enum_if -rw-r--r-- 1 mopar mopar 278900 2010-12-26 11:49 enum_if.o -rwxr-xr-x 1 mopar mopar 7702291 2010-12-26 11:49 fragmentation_test -rw-r--r-- 1 mopar mopar 552436 2010-12-26 11:49 fragmentation_test.o -rwxr-xr-x 1 mopar mopar 8147718 2010-12-26 11:49 make_torrent -rw-r--r-- 1 mopar mopar 684072 2010-12-26 11:49 make_torrent.o -rwxr-xr-x 1 mopar mopar 56686331 2010-12-26 11:49 simple_client -rw-r--r-- 1 mopar mopar 547232 2010-12-26 11:49 simple_client.o drwxr-xr-x 2 mopar mopar 4096 2010-12-26 11:45 src -rwxr-xr-x 1 mopar mopar 56663241 2010-12-26 11:49 upnp_test -rw-r--r-- 1 mopar mopar 511592 2010-12-26 11:49 upnp_test.o

(my username is mopar, I am the owner of the files)
